headline: EToro Stock Is Jumping. Earnings Surprised Despite Crypto Slump.
summary: Shares of eToro soared 20% early Tuesday morning after the brokerage firm reported fourth-quarter earnings that topped Wall Street estimates.  Adjusted EPS came in at 71 cents, compared to analyst expectations of 66 cents, according to estimates compiled by  FactSet  For the fourth quarter of 2024, eToro posted adjusted EPS of 79 cents.  On Tuesday, eToro also announced that its board of directors approved a $100 million increase to its share repurchase program.

headline: Bitcoin Price Falls. Why the Crypto Is Struggling to Break Back Above $70,000.
summary: The price of  Bitcoin  continued to drop Tuesday, remaining below $70,000.  The world’s largest cryptocurrency fell 0.6% to $68,356 over the past 24 hours, according to CoinDesk.  Coinbase  a cryptocurrency exchange, was up 1% in after-hours trading, while brokerage firm  Robinhood  climbed 0.1% and  Strategy  —the largest corporate holder of Bitcoin—was up 0.2%.
